Durban - National police minister, Bheki Cele, on Thursday paid a visit to the family of slain Chatsworth girl, Sadia Sukhraj. Cele was one of many high profile visitors to the Sukhraj family home in the wake of Sadia's death. 

AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

Sadia was shot in a botched hijacking on Monday morning. The nine-year-old girl was rushed to hospital but despite resuscitation efforts, she died a short while later. 



On Thursday, Cele first held a meeting at the Chatsworth police station. Although members of the media were invited to attend Cele's visit at midday at the police station, journalists had to wait outside while Cele spoke to police officials and management. The meeting was to discuss the riots that broke out at the police station on Monday. 















